  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In short</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">All 20 QuickBooks Online features, explained.</h2>
    </header>
    <p class="prose" id="kitchen-sink-b2-cardgrid-hub-summary">QuickBooks Online has dozens of features, but most businesses only need a clear answer to two questions: what does each feature actually do, and do I have it? This hub answers both &mdash; a plain-English page for all <strong>20 core QuickBooks Online features</strong>, grouped by how the work actually flows (money in, money out, banking, structure, work &amp; projects, planning &amp; reporting). Which features you have depends on your plan &mdash; Simple Start, Essentials, Plus, or Advanced &mdash; and some (inventory, classes, projects, budgeting) need Plus or Advanced. As an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; <strong>not Intuit</strong> &mdash; we don&rsquo;t sell QuickBooks; we configure and optimize these features in <em>your</em> file so the books stay accurate. Not sure which plan fits? See <a href="/quickbooks/which-plan-is-right/">which QuickBooks plan is right</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>


<section class="section" id="kitchen-sink-b2-cardgrid-hub-money-in">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Money in</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Getting paid.</h2><p class="section__lede">Billing customers and tracking what they owe you.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Invoices</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Create and send branded invoices, set terms, send recurring invoices, accept online payment, and track each one from sent to viewed to paid &mdash; QBO records the revenue and receivable automatically.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/invoices/">QBO invoices &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Estimates</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Build quotes for customers, track which were accepted, and convert an accepted estimate straight into an invoice without re-keying the line items.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/estimates/">QBO estimates &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Customers</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">The customer list that anchors your accounts-receivable &mdash; contact records, billing terms, sub-customers, statements, and the AR aging that shows who owes what.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/customers/">QBO customers &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Sales tax</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">QBO&rsquo;s automated sales-tax engine calculates rates by address and tracks what you owe &mdash; but it only works if products, customers, and nexus are set up correctly first.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/sales-tax/">QBO sales tax &rarr;</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="section section--alt" id="kitchen-sink-b2-cardgrid-hub-money-out">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Money out</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Paying the business.</h2><p class="section__lede">Tracking what you owe and what you spend.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Bills (A/P)</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Enter vendor bills, track due dates, and pay them &mdash; QBO records the accounts-payable balance so you see what&rsquo;s owed and when, instead of paying from memory.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/bills/">QBO bills &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Expenses</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Record and categorize what you spend &mdash; cash, card, and check purchases &mdash; with receipts attached, so the books reflect real costs and deductions stay defensible.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/expenses/">QBO expenses &rarr;</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="section" id="kitchen-sink-b2-cardgrid-hub-banking">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Banking</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Connecting and matching the bank.</h2><p class="section__lede">The engine that keeps the books tied to reality.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Bank feeds</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Connect bank and credit-card accounts so transactions flow into QBO automatically &mdash; the starting point, not the finish line; downloaded transactions still have to be reviewed and matched.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/bank-feeds/">QBO bank feeds &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Bank rules</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Auto-categorize recurring transactions from the bank feed by rule &mdash; a real time-saver, but bad rules quietly miscode the books, so they need setting up with care.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/bank-rules/">QBO bank rules &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Reconciliation</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Match QBO to your bank and credit-card statements every month so the balances are proven, not assumed. The single most important monthly habit &mdash; and the one most often skipped.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/reconciliation/">QBO reconciliation &rarr;</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="section section--alt" id="kitchen-sink-b2-cardgrid-hub-structure">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Items &amp; structure</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How the file is organized.</h2><p class="section__lede">The structure everything else is recorded against.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Chart of accounts</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">The backbone of the file &mdash; the list of accounts every transaction is coded to. Get this right and reports work; get it wrong and cleanup is inevitable.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/chart-of-accounts/">Chart of accounts &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Products &amp; services</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">The items you sell, mapped to income (and inventory) accounts &mdash; what makes invoices, estimates, and sales-tax automation actually work correctly.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/products-services/">Products &amp; services &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Inventory</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Track stock quantities and value with QBO&rsquo;s FIFO inventory &mdash; available on Plus and Advanced. Useful for product businesses; not a fit for everyone.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/inventory/">QBO inventory &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Classes</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Tag transactions by segment &mdash; location, department, fund, property &mdash; for profit-and-loss by class. Plus and Advanced only, and only useful if applied consistently.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/classes/">QBO classes &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Custom fields</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Add your own fields to forms and records to capture data QBO doesn&rsquo;t track by default. Limited on lower plans; far more flexible on Advanced.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/custom-fields/">QBO custom fields &rarr;</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="section" id="kitchen-sink-b2-cardgrid-hub-work-projects">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Work &amp; projects</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Job costing and payroll.</h2><p class="section__lede">Tracking profitability by job and paying your team.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Projects</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">See income, costs, and profitability per job &mdash; the closest thing QBO has to job costing. Available on Plus and Advanced.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/projects/">QBO projects &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Time tracking</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Log billable and payroll hours against customers and projects &mdash; built in on QBO, with deeper tracking through QuickBooks Time on higher tiers.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/time-tracking/">QBO time tracking &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Payroll</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">QuickBooks Payroll is a separate paid add-on from Intuit that runs payroll and files payroll taxes inside QBO. We explain how it works and where setup goes wrong &mdash; we are not Intuit.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/payroll/">QBO payroll &rarr;</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="section section--alt" id="kitchen-sink-b2-cardgrid-hub-planning">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Planning &amp; reporting</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Seeing where you stand.</h2><p class="section__lede">Turning the data into decisions.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Reports</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Profit and loss, balance sheet, AR/AP aging, and more &mdash; QBO&rsquo;s reports are only as accurate as the data feeding them, which is why setup and reconciliation come first.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/reports/">QBO reports &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Budgeting</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Build a budget in QBO and compare actuals against it month by month. Available on Plus and Advanced &mdash; useful once the chart of accounts is clean.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/budgeting/">QBO budgeting &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Cash flow planner</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">QBO&rsquo;s forward-looking cash-flow view projects money in and out over the coming weeks &mdash; a planning tool, not a guarantee, and only as good as the underlying data.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/online/features/cash-flow-planner/">Cash flow planner &rarr;</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<section class="section" id="kitchen-sink-b2-cardgrid-hub-vs-alternatives">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">QuickBooks vs alternatives</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks against the other tools.</h2><p class="section__lede">Five honest, side-by-side reads. We prefer QuickBooks and we say so &mdash; but where one of these fits your business better, we name it.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">QuickBooks vs Xero</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">The closest head-to-head. Xero is a genuinely strong double-entry cloud platform with clean multi-currency &mdash; we tell you the kinds of businesses where it&rsquo;s the better call, and where QuickBooks&rsquo; ecosystem and ProAdvisor depth win.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/compare/quickbooks-vs-xero/">QuickBooks vs Xero &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">QuickBooks vs Wave</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Wave is free, and for a true solo side-hustle that can be the right answer &mdash; we say so plainly. We&rsquo;re honest about where Wave runs out of room as you grow and what you give up at the free tier.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/compare/quickbooks-vs-wave/">QuickBooks vs Wave &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">QuickBooks vs Sage</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Sage is a broad family of products, from small-business cloud to mid-market ERP. We compare like-for-like and flag the cases where a Sage product genuinely outfits a more complex or industry-specific operation.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/compare/quickbooks-vs-sage/">QuickBooks vs Sage &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">QuickBooks vs FreshBooks</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">FreshBooks is built around invoicing and is a delight for freelancers and client-services solos &mdash; we&rsquo;ll tell you when that focus is exactly right, and where its lighter accounting depth becomes a ceiling.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/compare/quickbooks-vs-freshbooks/">QuickBooks vs FreshBooks &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">QuickBooks vs Zoho Books</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">Zoho Books is capable and shines inside the wider Zoho suite. We&rsquo;re straight about when that ecosystem pull makes Zoho the smarter fit, and where QuickBooks&rsquo; accountant network gives you more support.</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/compare/quickbooks-vs-zoho-books/">QuickBooks vs Zoho Books &rarr;</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
